@node "Main" "Amiga Echo Disk 6"
             *** A M I G A  E C H O  D I S K  VI ***

Welcome back to the EchoDisks!  As before, this is a collection of pictures
from many online personalities of the FidoNet Amiga Echo, Joyce "My kingdom
for an Ethernet" Divina presiding.

This disk has some repeat appearances, some new pics of old regulars, and a
few totally new (but game) faces in the crowd.

As you may have noticed, I'm now spreading the EchoDisk as an AmigaGuide
file.  If you do not already have AmigaGuide.Library in your LIBS:
directory, it is freely downloadable from several points around the galaxy.

In no particular order:

          @{"Paula Lieberman" system "amigadisk6:c/vt amigadisk6:pics/paula_lieberman.jpg"}       @{"Rich & Carol Koster" link "Rich Koster" 0}
          @{"   Juan F Amiga" link "Juan F Amiga" 0}       @{"Millie Walker Bush " link "Millie Walker Bush" 0}
          @{"    Dan Barrett" link "Dan B." 0}       @{"J.T. West          " link "JTWest" 0}
          @{"John Covington " link "Covington" 0}       @{"William Near       " link "WillNear" 0}
          @{"Micheal Fierro " link "Zaphod" 0}

                           and

               @{"Skipper Smith with Fred Fish" link "Skipper&Fred" 0}

Many of these pics were digitized from pics sent to me, Orin, or Asha (maybe
we oughta start putting her address in here, too! ;-) In this case, it was
Paula, Micheal, and the pic of Fred Fish and Skipper.  We also got one from
Skal, but until I get a yes or no on a bio from him, I'm saving him back for
later (besides, we were out of room!). Juan F., Millie, JT, Bill, Rich, and
John all supplied thiers on disk -- some which had to be translated from
24-bit formats to keep in the "one disk many pics" format.  Dan Barrett's
was posted on AmiNet in the PICS/IRC directory, I think.

For my next trick, I will perform the task of generating AmigaEchoDisk
Elite!  AEDE will be a revamping of all the previous disks in AmigaGuide
format, intended for hard drive installation only.  All the disks will be
combined into one large AmigaGuide document, and where JPEGs exist, I will
use those -- nice thing about ViewTek is that it will give you the best
output you can handle, so JPeg is a great format for us ECS users as well as
the AGA crowd.  By the time I finish translating the first 6 disks to that
format, I should have enough material to come out with a seventh installment
of the EchoDisks, which will feature Skal Loret, Asha's wedding pic (I can
hear the hearts breaking from here!), and a small tribute to Jay Miner, as
well as any other lunatics we can talk into this!  Stay tuned!

Don't forget, if you would like to be featured on a future echodisk, please
submit your picture forthwith!

